Business Brief -- American Health Properties:
   Firm Will Allow a Hospital
   To Delay Interest Payment
He said the operations of the 175-bed psychiatric hospital
aren't generating enough cash to fully service the debt this
year, but he said he is comfortable that "long-term, the
hospital will be able to service the debt."
   The company said it can't predict when the talks will be
completed with Four Winds Inc., the hospital's owner and
manager. Mr. Diener said he doesn't believe the hospital's
problems will affect American Health's earnings or dividends.